<P>
KING ORDERS 1990 ELECTIONS PUT OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elections that had been scheduled for September, 1990, have been postponed for 
at least two years in hopes that the disputed Western Sahara will be able to 
join in the voting, King Hassan II announced. Hassan also called on the United 
Nations to speed up plans for a referendum in the disputed territory to see 
whether residents want to live under Moroccan rule. 
</P>
