<P>
INQUIRY ON POLITICAL SLAYINGS DEMANDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The family of two slain human rights lawyers demanded an independent judicial 
inquiry into allegations that South African police carried out political 
murders. Mbasa Mxenge, 25, asked President Frederik W. de Klerk to order an 
inquiry into the killings of his father, Griffiths, in 1981 and his mother, 
Victoria, in 1985. An ex-police captain has said he led a death squad from 
1980-1982. 
</P>
