<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A natural gas main ruptured Wednesday in Clairemont near Mt. Aguilar and Mt. 
Alifan drives, forcing the evacuation of 40 people, a San Diego Fire Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Workers at a nearby office building were evacuated and a three-block area near 
the main break was closed to traffic after the 8:50 a.m. leak, spokesman Larry 
Stewart said. 
</P>
<P>
The 2-inch line broke when a private contractor was doing road work in the 
area, Stewart said. San Diego Gas &amp; Electric crews took an hour to "pinch 
off" the break before workers were allowed to return. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters said there were no explosions or injuries as the crews repaired 
the broken main. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
