<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With a simple 3, 8, 20, 25, 40, 48, James P. Carroll of El Cajon won more than 
$5 million in Saturday's California Lottery game, officials announced 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Specifically, Carroll won $5,211,954 of a $10.4-million jackpot. He purchased 
his winning ticket at the 7-Eleven store at 1296 N. 2nd St., said Bruce 
Cherubin, district manager for the State Lottery. 
</P>
<P>
Carroll will receive annually $260,597 minus 20% in federal taxes for the next 
20 years, Cherubin said. Carroll, shunning all publicity of his big win, will 
get his first check through the mail within the next couple of weeks instead of 
at the usual check presentation ceremony, Cherubin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
