<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Nice Way With Kids: Former "Hill Street Blues" television star Taurean 
Blacque was honored by Los Angeles County supervisors for adopting nine 
children that agencies deemed hard to place. "I love the kids and they needed 
homes. I was blessed to do it," said Blacque, whose children range from 10 
months to 11 years, after accepting a commendation from the board. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
