<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GLENDALE MAN ACCUSED OF MOLESTING GIRL, 8 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Criminal charges were filed Wednesday against a Glendale man accused of 
molesting an 8-year-old girl during a break-in at her parents' house last week, 
Glendale police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man took the girl from her bed and removed her clothes but fled when she 
screamed, Investigator Ron Insalaco said. 
</P>
<P>
The man allegedly burglarized another residence in his apartment building in 
the 1900 block of Vassar Avenue and is believed to have molested a woman during 
another burglary earlier this month, Insalaco said. 
</P>
<P>
The man told police his name is Ramon Hernandez, Insalaco said. But officers 
believe that is an assumed name because a check of his fingerprints revealed he 
has 21 known aliases, Insalaco said. 
</P>
<P>
He recently moved to Glendale from Oakland and appears to be in his mid-30s, 
Insalaco said. The man, who has a lengthy criminal record, including two prison 
terms, was being held in Los Angeles County Jail in lieu of $250,000 bail, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
After his arrest Monday at his apartment, police found $16,000 in cash and a 
loaded handgun in his car, Insalaco said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
