</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: STRICT CONTROLS SOUGHT ON ADULT BOOKSTORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles city attorney's office filed a lawsuit Wednesday seeking strict 
controls on the operation of a North Hollywood adult bookstore where police 
have made 21 lewd-conduct arrests and several prostitution arrests in the last 
two years. 
</P>
<P>
The J&amp;B Bookstore in the 10900 block of Vanowen Street has been "a center 
for lewd conduct and prostitution" and needs to develop "a degree of decorum," 
said Ted Goldstein, a spokesman for the city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
Store Manager Steven Wiener and owners Ambros and Friederike Dragojevic, and 
Dan and Silvia Gerstner could not be reached for comment Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The suit accused them of creating a public nuisance under a section of the 
state penal code called the Red Light Abatement Law, Goldstein said. 
</P>
<P>
The civil suit asks a judge to order the store's operators to install more 
lights and to hire a 24-hour private guard to patrol the premises, Goldstein 
said. No court date has been set. 
</P>
</TEXT>
