<P>
The Sunkist Invitational track and field meet is offering a $100,000 bonus to 
an athlete who can break the men's or women's world indoor mile record in the 
meet Jan. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Athletes scheduled to compete are Paula Ivan of Romania, the 1988 Olympic gold 
medalist at 1,500 meters, and PattiSue Plumer, who this year set the American 
record at 5,000 meters. In the men's race are 1988 U.S. Olympians Steve Scott 
and Jeff Atkinson. 
</P>
<P>
