<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: POMONA; 
</P>
<P>
PRICE CLUB TO GET CITY LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pomona Redevelopment Agency, which paid $518,000 for a half-acre lot at the 
northwest corner of Garey Avenue and Philadelphia Street, will resell it to the 
owners of the nearby Price Club for $66,648 under an agreement made four years 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement approved this week by the City Council, acting as the 
Redevelopment Agency, carries out a commitment made in 1985 when the Price Co. 
agreed to open an outlet in Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
The company will use the lot and adjoining property to develop a commercial 
center, Price Club Plaza, with at least 35,000 square feet of space. The 
agreement calls for the plaza to be completed in 22 months. 
</P>
<P>
City officials said that, although the property is being sold at a discount, 
the city expects to profit from sales and property taxes and business license 
fees for the new stores and from increases in taxable sales at the existing 
Price Club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
