<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Luz Villarreal 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Gabriel High School Grad Nite Planning Committee is urging parents to 
become involved with the senior all-night party this year. 
</P>
<P>
Parents sponsor fund-raisers, solicit donations and services and chaperon the 
event, Chairwoman Rita De La Rosa said. 
</P>
<P>
Seniors have three choices of activities this year: Disneyland, a cruise in 
Long Beach Harbor and a "Dial 'M' Murder Mystery," a game in which a series of 
murder mysteries are solved by participants. Voting will take place Monday, De 
La Rosa said. 
</P>
<P>
For the last three years, seniors have gone to Disneyland for their Grad Nite 
party, but attendence has declined, De La Rosa said. 
</P>
<P>
Because students will be choosing their activity this year, De La Rosa said she 
hopes more will attend. 
</P>
<P>
"The more in attendance, the (fewer who) will be out in the streets being 
exposed to alcohol," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Committee members are concentrating on reducing the costs for the seniors by 
sponsoring car washes and raffles as fund-raisers. 
</P>
<P>
The next committee meeting will be Tuesday at 8:30 p.m. at Marie Callender's, 
518 W. Las Tunas Drive, San Gabriel. 
</P>
<P>
Interested parents can call (818) 308-2356 or (818) 284-8509 for information. 
Luz Villarreal 
</P>
</TEXT>
