<P>
BAY AREA TO HOST ARTS 'FESTIVAL 2000' IN 1990 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Francisco will host next year the first-ever "Festival 2000: A Celebration 
of Cultural Diversity," a $2.2-million, 23-day arts festival highlighting the 
Bay Area's non-traditional musicians, actors, dancers, film makers and artists. 
</P>
<P>
The festival is scheduled to start Oct. 6, 1990, and will take over many of San 
Francisco's concert halls, galleries, theaters and public areas for 45 events 
featuring about 1,000 artists. 
</P>
