<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY'S DIDIER NAMED TO JUDGESHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daniel J. Didier, deputy county counsel for Orange County, was named Wednesday 
by Gov. George Deukmejian to a judgeship on the Orange County Municipal Court 
in Westminster. 
</P>
<P>
In his work for the county, Didier, 43, served as a liaison between the Board 
of Supervisors and the special counsel representing John Wayne Airport. He has 
been a deputy county counsel since 1977. 
</P>
<P>
Didier, of Santa Ana, holds a bachelor's degree from Cal State Fullerton and a 
law degree from Western State University. He also earned a master's degree in 
business taxation from USC. 
</P>
<P>
Didier's new job pays $82,054 annually. He replaces Judge Floyd H. Schenk, who 
was promoted to Orange County Superior Court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
JUDGES -- ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
