<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Health Care Systems: The Irvine-based prepaid dental plan operator 
reported improvement in both earnings and revenue for the third quarter and 
nine-month period. Net income for the third quarter totaled $51,107, contrasted 
with a loss of $22,019 for the comparable 1988 period. Revenue rose 85%, to 
$2.4 million from $1.3 million. For the nine-month period, net income was 
$228,619, compared to $8,956 a year earlier. Revenue increased 84%, to $6.7 
million from $3.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112389-0193 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 139183 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 23, 1989, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 5; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
95 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Seahawk Oil International Inc., Irvine, reported that it has completed the 
sale of all its producing and nonproducing oil and gas assets in the United 
States to Pittencrieff America Inc. for about $4.5 million. The company said it 
will continue to be involved in international oil and gas exploration through 
its majority share-holding in Seahawk Overseas Exploration Corp. At a special 
shareholders meeting last week, a name change for the company to Seahawk 
Capital Corp. and a doubling of the corporation's authorized shares to 50 
million were also approved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
