65 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CMS Enhancements Inc. of Tustin said it has met the listing criteria and has 
applied to list its securities on the New York Stock Exchange. The company, 
whose common stock is currently traded on the NASDAQ National Market System, 
said it expects to be listed on the Big Board by mid-December. CMS produces and 
distributes memory storage devices and accessories for personal computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
